methods.empty:
Get an empty MutableRowSet.

:return: (io.deephaven.engine.v2.utils.MutableRowSet) A new MutableRowSet containing no rows
methods.flat:
Get a flat MutableRowSet containing the row key range [0, size), or an empty row
 set if size <= 0.

:param size: (long) - The size of the MutableRowSet to create
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.v2.utils.MutableRowSet) A flat MutableRowSet containing the row key range [0, size) or an empty
         row set if the size <= 0
methods.fromKeys:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**

Get a MutableRowSet containing the specified row keys.
 
 The provided TLongList is sorted and then passed to a RowSetBuilderSequential.

*Overload 1*  
  :param rowKeys: (long...) - The row keys to include
  :return: (io.deephaven.engine.v2.utils.MutableRowSet) A new MutableRowSet containing the specified row keys
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param rowKey: (long) - The row key to include
  :return: (io.deephaven.engine.v2.utils.MutableRowSet) A new MutableRowSet containing the specified row key
  
*Overload 3*  
  :param rowKeys: (gnu.trove.list.TLongList) - A TLongList. Note that this list is mutated within the method!
  :return: (io.deephaven.engine.v2.utils.RowSet) A new MutableRowSet containing the values from rowKeys
methods.fromRange:
Create a MutableRowSet containing the continuous range [firstRowKey, lastRowKey].

:param firstRowKey: (long) - The first row key in the continuous range
:param lastRowKey: (long) - The last row key in the continuous range
:return: (io.deephaven.engine.v2.utils.MutableRowSet) A new MutableRowSet containing the specified row key range
